                                                   Appeals Commissioner

      A STAFF REPORTER
           
	Calcutta: The Appeals Commissioner will be appointed from the members of the ICC Code of Conduct Commission. For obvious reasons, the Indian and Australian representatives will not be considered. 
    
	The Code of Conduct Commission comprises Hon.Michael Beloff QC (chairman), Richie Benaud (Australia), Ajmalul Hossain QC (Bangladesh), Sir Oliver Popplewell (England), Goolam Vahanvati (India), Justice John Hansen (New Zealand), Mohammed Aslam Sanjrani (Pakistan), Justice Albie Sachs (South Africa), Nishantha Ranatunga (Sri Lanka), Justice Adrian Saunders (West Indies), Advocate Moses Mtombeni (Zimbabwe), Sharad Rao (Kenya), Frank Sowman (Ireland), Jim Young (Scotland), Stindar K. Lal QC (Canada), Marc Wetherhill (Bermuda) and Stevan van Hoogstraten (Netherlands). 
                                                   
